NAME
wutconv - converts input lines to Windows or Unix line endings.
SYNOPSIS
wutconv {-u|-w} [-v] [TEXT_FILE_NAME ...]
wutconv {-h|-V}
wutconv [OPTIONS] [TEXT_FILE_NAME ...]
DESCRIPTION
Converts the line endings in one or more text files to Windows or Unix format,
i.e. LFCR or LF.
If no text files are specified on the command line, stdin is converted to
stdout.
OPTIONS
-h, --help	Displays usage information.
-u, --unix	Convert to Unix line endings.
-v, --verbose	Display verbose output.
-V, --version	Displays version information.
-w, --windows	Convert to Windows line endings.
TEXT_FILE_NAME	List of text file names. If blank, stdin and stdout are used.
EXIT STATUS
0 - Success
.br
1 - General error
.br
64 - Command line usage error
.br
66 - Cannot open input
.br
77 - Permission denied
